reviews.review_text: I gave a very negative review regarding the quality of the food, the level of customer service at this location about one year ago. It was warranted.  It was terrible. For the past 2 months I ve been coming back here late at night, everything has changed.   They tell you to wait a few mins for your order but that s because they are cooking it fresher for you. Even though it seems they are still understaffed at times, the STAFF is putting in the effort to make each and every order the way it should be.  Fresh, hot and with a smile. Dear owner and managers, I know margins are very low right now but please try to do your best to have enough staff on to help them do their jobs better and also happier. Keep up the good work and thanks for doing a great job serving your local community!
Outdoor seating is super nice on a sunny day. The self ordering kiosks were all off when I visited.
Friendly service every time!  Marcella   is my favourite hostess! She makes me feel quite welcome here at McDonalds! Thank you Marcella and friends! Glenn
Some of the nicest and FASTEST staff Ive come across in a McDonalds - a lovely experience!

Picked up lunch via the drive thru and was pleasantly surprised how much I miss the food. Attendants were friendly and efficient. Maybe the 10 cent bag is a good idea to hold the fries from flying around in the car.

The cashier didnt want to change my drink, ask with no ice and he gave me one full of ice. He told me that I didnt request no ice and he couldnt give me another one, told him to throw the ice and fill it with come the same cup. Finally another girl from the staff did it.

Usually I feel most of the Mcdonald s restaurant seems like a burger factory more than a restaurant to me but this location is awesome. I would say just bcz of wonderful staff members, here staff is so polite & awesome service makes it different, clean restaurant along with enough parking.
Great service at this location. Online order took fast and quality was all right, but not the best look. Nice clean store. Parking available on site.

The taller Caucasian manager with dyed blonde hair is delightful and enthusiastic, as is the caucasian woman with brown hair at the cashier station on 1st shift. They all do their best with the high demand: Its the only drive-thru in downtown Ladner. Its always busy in the early morning and on weekends. The ambiance is typical McDs, & the interior had a major renovation recently. Seniors enjoying their discount coffee & Trades workers picking up a fast lunch.

The food was divine. Kudos to the chefs. Only one thing, though, that s I found weird about this restaurant. There was a man lurking in the corner of the the restaurant  I took a seat across from him, introduced myself, and he told me folks called him the Bush Man. He seemed to be a rather kind man, though a bit mysterious. We seemed to have ordered the same thing  a McDouble meal, large fries, and large Diet Coke. He told me,  Don t trust that maidens will find you, you must find them yourself.  I was reading through other reviews and noticed other stuff had a similar experience. Weird. Uncanny.

I met a man here who called himself The Bush Man. We both ordered the same item: Double Cheeseburger with Large Fries. Upon us sitting down, he leaned forward and told me something of which I had never forgotten: Dont Trust that Maidens will find you. You must look for them yourself. Upon him completing his sentence, he was gone. Meal and All. But his wisdom in which he bestowed me... it was nearly better than the meal I had. 10/10, I am enlightened.
There were some entitled people that came in just after me; the staff handled them courteously and with great patience. Big props to the team here!
Usually given the wrong items lol so check your bag in drive thru before you drive away But they fix mistakes hassle free which is nice Food
Love the revamp of the place. I mean its still a McDonalds but now it looks way better.
An excellent place to walk around beautiful pathways and see nature at its finest.
Lot of sitting space, and quick service.  Food and taste etc are pretty standard as McDonald.
Our son had an amazing birthday party here! Staff was great at helpful! Thank you Arseen you were awesome!! Kid-friendliness: Awesome place to have birthday party
Very reliable in quality and expectations. What you would expect for fast food. Best price for coffee
well served.. thank you

The mobile app didnt allow a certain payment option and fortunately the employee thought to ask the manager. Quick to respond, the manager Trent arrived and I was able to get my friend Harold a lot more for the price when he needed it most. Thanks McDonalds for helping my friend who has disabilities. You made the evening special and your genuine care for others is admired greatly. Thank you.

Went in around 7:30 on a Friday. Quiet and quick service. I used my free coffee card to get a ice cream cone, the cashier was so nice about it. The service was super fast, after I payed I got my food right away. Super happy with my service
This is the cleanest McDonalds!! Tables that are sanitized are clearly displayed with a sign. Staff is constantly cleaning, and sanitizing during the busy lunch hour, too. I am very impressed.
Super delicious food thanks

If this is the Ladner lo atiin, best location in Delta/Surrey Vegetarian options: Better selection of healthy vegetables Parking: Little difficult to drive in an out Kid-friendliness: Better seating and and sanitizing stns that were lower. No indoor playground, so no stress to play. We ate in peace Wheelchair accessibility: Noticed but did not need to utilize

I come here all the time. I have never been inside but they have dual lane drive thru and are always been quick with my order. They have never missed anything from my order and get it right the first time!

This is my favorite McDonalds location.  They are the only ones who have never forgotten to add mayonnaise to my breakfast sandwiches, and they never charge extra for it.  They are not perfect, sometimes they are slow to give out a simple order, such as just a cup of coffee.  Very often, the self serve kiosks dont issue receipts.  These are problems at every McDonalds, not just this one.

I seriously recommend to go here customer service is perfect I didn t saw this type of customer service in my life . 15 minutes ago 2 Indian girls work at the front she really gave very quick service.  I would like to say that if we wanna save time then go on this Mac Donald.
Nothing compares to Canadas beef, and McDonalds is waaay better here than it is down south. Keep up the good work!
Ive been going here for 5 years on my way to work. Theyve never scewed up my order or taken a long time. If you leave a bad review for this McDonalds you are a TRASH PERSON.
Delicious food and wonderful service. Furthermore, this restaurant is situated in a beautiful forested area, and is in a heritage home. Definitely my favorite restaurant in Maple Ridge and Mission

The McDonalds in Ladner looks very inviting from the outside, the interior is spacious & comfortable, & the staff are friendly. I had a delicious Country Chicken Burger, & my wife had a lovely Greek Salad. I would highly recommend this McDonalds Restaurant!
Food was hot always a plus at McDonalds the service was great!! Kid-friendliness: Playground Food : 4/5 |
Taste better than all McD in Richmond Clean and non slippery floor
The food was great the coffee was too sweet I asked for 3 and four before and it didnt taste like that

So i went for a late night meal here as there was nothing else open, i ordered a mcdouble combo and requested a spritopia for those of you who dont know of this it is strawberry frutopia and sprite mixed, for the correct taste you must have 1/3 frutopia and 2/3 sprite to achieve the ultimate flavour, I was told this was not possible because once the drink is entered the machine will automatically fill the cup..I then presisted to ask for this mixture and the gentleman working the cash worked some magic and completed my request!! For this I commend you with 5 stars, thanks and goodnight
Their chicken is superb and love tge facts you dont have to have French Fries with other sides available
Didnt charge for tartar sauce. Also saw the Asst manager help out some elderly folks with contacting their family on her phone.

A nice quaint local McDonalds. If youre into McDonalds architecture this one is a classic styled restaurant with a play-place. The staff here can very from youth to seniors and theyre all generally cheerful and friendly.
It is a busy location (parking lot were full), but employees work efficiently for all customers.  Friendly staffs and clean dining area.
Good service. Had a tasty caramel latte. 1$ ice cream is delicious. Kid-friendliness: My son always enjoy at play place.
